renderOnSave.title: Render Preview on Save
renderOnSave.description: Render the Panel preview automatically after saving the notebook

saveState.title: Save Jupyter widget state in notebooks
saveState.description: Automatically save Jupyter widget state when a notebook is saved.

schema.title: AI SDK Chat Kernel
schema.description: Settings for the AI SDK Chat Kernel

defaultProvider.title: Default Provider
defaultProvider.description: The AI provider to use. 'built-in-ai' uses Chrome Built-in AI with WebLLM fallback. Other options include openai, anthropic, google, or any custom provider name.

defaultModel.title: Default Model
defaultModel.description: The model to use when the kernel is first initialized. For built-in-ai: use 'prompt-api' for Chrome AI or WebLLM model names. Use %chat list <provider> to see available models.

apiKey.title: API Key
apiKey.description: API key for the selected provider (e.g., OpenAI, Anthropic, Google). Not needed for 'built-in-ai' provider. The key is stored in browser local storage.

schema.title: WebLLM Chat Kernel
schema.description: Settings for the WebLLM Chat Kernel

defaultModel.title: Default Model
defaultModel.description: The WebLLM model to use when the kernel is first initialized. Once a cell is executed, the model is locked and can only be changed using the %chat model <name> magic command. Use %chat list in a notebook to see all available models.
